			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Currently there are three different command line validator tools, one
for each architecture:

 * ncval: x86-32
 * ncval_sfi: x86-64
 * arm-ncval-core: ARM

They do not share code and they have different interfaces.

There are also two wrapper programs for decorating the validator's
output:

 * ncval_annotate.py: wrapper for x86-32 validator
 * validation-report.py: wrapper for ARM validator

We should unify these tools so that one executable will validate code
for all architectures, and can be built for all architectures.
